Bobby Clack (actor) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bobby_Clack_(actor) 0 Bobby Clack (January 3, 1926 - April 3, 1986) was an American film actor during the Western B-movies era. Sometimes he is credited as Bobby Clark or Dusty Dixon. His father, Arnold Clack, also was a film actor. Clack was born in Spiro, Oklahoma, and died in Oregon at the age of 60.
